subSubSection.paragraph:
A poorly preserved plate, showing only the basal bone lamella, is interpreted here as a possible PNu plate (
Figs 3B
; 
4B
). It is roughly trapezoidal, with at least two distinct overlap areas for the Nu and lateral (L) plates, respectively (oaNu, oaL, 
Fig. 4B
). As far as as can be seen, its overall shape would agree with that of the PNu plate of 

Yunnanolepis

.

